    {
      "id": "PopularPost147087",
      "post_content": "1. [Ertai, the Corrupted](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ertai, the Corrupted)  \n2. [Lullmage Mentor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lullmage Mentor)  \n3. [Sea Scryer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sea Scryer)  \n4. [Carnival of Souls](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Carnival of Souls)  \n5. [Intruder Alarm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Intruder Alarm)  \n6. [Soul Warden](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Soul Warden)  \n  \n  \nOther recommendations: A sacrificial creature to start the process.  \n  \nThe process:   \nA. The opponent casts a spell, you pay ![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol) and sacrifice a creature to counter it.  \nB. Once this resolves, you just countered an opponents spell, so [Lullmage Mentor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lullmage Mentor) activates giving you a creature token.  \nC. Since you just got a creature, [Carnival of Souls](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Carnival of Souls) takes 1 life, and gives you one black mana.  \nD. Again, since you just got a creature, [Soul Warden](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Soul Warden) gives you back the life you lost in Step C.  \nE. Yet again, since you just got a creature, [Intruder Alarm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Intruder Alarm) untaps everything, including Ertai and the Sea Scryer  \nF. You have ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) in your mana pool. If another spell is cast, tap the ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Tonymitsu",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost147087\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">1.  <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ertai, the Corrupted\">Ertai, the Corrupted</a><br/>2.  <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lullmage Mentor\">Lullmage Mentor</a><br/>3.  <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sea Scryer\">Sea Scryer</a><br/>4.  <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Carnival of Souls\">Carnival of Souls</a><br/>5.  <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Intruder Alarm\">Intruder Alarm</a><br/>6.  <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Soul Warden\">Soul Warden</a><br/><br/><br/>Other recommendations:  A sacrificial creature to start the process.<br/><br/>The process:  <br/>A.  The opponent casts a spell, you pay <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=U&amp;type=symbol\"/> and sacrifice a creature to counter it.<br/>B.  Once this resolves, you just countered an opponents spell, so <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lullmage Mentor\">Lullmage Mentor</a> activates giving you a creature token.<br/>C.  Since you just got a creature, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Carnival of Souls\">Carnival of Souls</a> takes 1 life, and gives you one black mana.<br/>D.  Again, since you just got a creature, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Soul Warden\">Soul Warden</a> gives you back the life you lost in Step C.<br/>E.  Yet again, since you just got a creature, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Intruder Alarm\">Intruder Alarm</a> untaps everything, including Ertai and the Sea Scryer<br/>F.  You have <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/> in your mana poo